---
layout: base.njk
title: 'time machine'
versions:
    - year: 2022
      url: 'https://cv-angular.maltebaer.vercel.app'
      tools:
          - name: 'angular'
          - name: 'typescript'
          - name: 'tailwind ui'
    - year: 2021
      url: 'https://cv-vue.maltebaer.vercel.app'
      tools:
          - name: 'vue'
          - name: 'tailwind css'
---

<main class="region stack">
    <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
    <p>
        when i want to learn something new, try an unfamiliar concept, or just have fun
        coding, this is my project. it's a simple resume. but because it's a simple
        project, i can focus on implementing my ideas.
    </p>

    <p>
        <a
            href="https://hicks.design/journal/bill-oddie"
            target="__blank"
        >
            jon hicks
        </a>
        inspired me to create a time machine. i like the idea of hosting your own little
        internet archive.
    </p>

    <blockquote>
        It’s a lot like an embarrassing family photo, but I’m owning it!
    </blockquote>

    {% for version in versions %}
    <article class="flow">
        <h2>{{ version.year }}</h2>

        <div class="resizer">
            <iframe
                src="{{ version.url }}"
                allow="fullscreen"
            ></iframe>
        </div>

        <dl
            class="cluster"
            style="--cluster-gap: var(--space-xs)"
        >
            <dt>tools:</dt>
            {% for tool in version.tools %}
            <dd class="badge">{{ tool.name }}</dd>
            {% endfor %}
        </dl>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
</main>
